hopla get - group command

For more help use `hopla --help get {SUB_COMMAND}`

syntax:
    hopla [global_options] get {SUB_COMMAND}...

SUPPORTED SUB COMMANDS:
    hopla get user-auth       -- get user authentication info
    hopla get user-info       -- get information about the user (with optional filter functionality)
    hopla get user-stats      -- get the user's stats (e.g. lvl and experience)
    hopla get user-inventory  -- get the user's inventory  (e.g. pets)

